         <abstract>
            <p>In "Weighted Average vs. True Cost of Capital" on pages 56-60 of the Autumn 1973 issue of "Financial Management," Professor James S. Ang demonstrated a bias in the weighted average calculation of cost of capital and developed a method for calculating the "true" cost for the familiar constant dividend growth model. Three comments were received in reply. The respondents included Professor Raymond R. Reilly of the University of Michigan, Professor Eugene F. Brigham of the University of Florida, and Professors Linke and Kim of the University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign. Their comments and Professor Ang's response to them are presented in this article.</p>
         </abstract>
